{
  "id" : 747,
  "songNumber" : 135,
  "title" : "I CARE NOT TODAY WHAT THE MORROW MAY BRING",
  "language" : "english",
  "originalKey" : "D",
  "capo" : 0,
  "bpm" : 0,
  "timeSignature" : "4/4",
  "hashtags" : [ ],
  "sections" : [ {
    "type" : "verse",
    "label" : "VERSE 1",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "I care not today what the morrow may bring,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 37
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "If shadow or sunshine or rain,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 3
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 25
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "The Lord I know ruleth o'er everything,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 28
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "And all of my worry is vain.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 23
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "Living by faith, in Jesus above,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 27
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Trusting, confiding in His great love;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 33
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "I am safe from all harm, in His sheltering arm.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "I'm living by faith and feel no alarm.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 32
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "Though tempest may blow and the storm clouds arise,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 7
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 46
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Obscuring the brightness of life,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 2
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 28
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "I'm never alarmed at the overcast skies,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 34
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "The Master looks on at the strife.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 27
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "I know that He safely will carry me through,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 2
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 36
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "No matter what evils betide,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 3
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 23
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Why should I then care, though the tempest may blow,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 47
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "If Jesus walks close to my side.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 3
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 27
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : ""
    }, {
      "text" : "Our Lord will return to this earth some sweet day,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 46
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Our troubles will then all be o'er,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 30
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "The Master so gently will lead us away,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 35
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Beyond that blest heavenly shore.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 2
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 27
      } ]
    } ]
  } ]
}